"Stige L.C., Chan K.-S., Zhang Z., Frank D., Stenseth N.C.","Thousand-year-long Chinese time series reveals climatic forcing of decadal locust dynamics",2007,"Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America","104","41",,"16188","16193",,,10.1073/pnas.0706813104,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-35548941870&partnerID=40&md5=6ee8584408fecd63ff9a6d5e5ac776be","Centre for Ecological and Evolutionary Synthesis (CEES), Department of Biology, University of Oslo, Blindern, 0316 Oslo, Norway; Department of Statistics and Actuarial Science, University of Iowa, 263 Schaeffer Hall, Iowa City, IA 52242, United States; State Key Laboratory of Integrated Management of Pest Insects and Rodents in Agriculture, Institute of Zoology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Tatun Road, Chao Yang District, Beijing 100101, China; Swiss Federal Research Institute for Forest, Snow, and Landscape Research, Zuercherstrasse 111, 8903 Birmensdorf, Switzerland","Stige, L.C., Centre for Ecological and Evolutionary Synthesis (CEES), Department of Biology, University of Oslo, Blindern, 0316 Oslo, Norway; Chan, K.-S., Department of Statistics and Actuarial Science, University of Iowa, 263 Schaeffer Hall, Iowa City, IA 52242, United States; Zhang, Z., State Key Laboratory of Integrated Management of Pest Insects and Rodents in Agriculture, Institute of Zoology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Tatun Road, Chao Yang District, Beijing 100101, China; Frank, D., Swiss Federal Research Institute for Forest, Snow, and Landscape Research, Zuercherstrasse 111, 8903 Birmensdorf, Switzerland; Stenseth, N.C., Centre for Ecological and Evolutionary Synthesis (CEES), Department of Biology, University of Oslo, Blindern, 0316 Oslo, Norway","For >1,000 years, Chinese officials have recorded the annual abundance of the oriental migratory locust Locusta migratoria manilensis, with the ultimate aim of predicting locust outbreaks. Linking these records with temperature and precipitation reconstructions for the period 957-1956, we show that decadal mean locust abundance is highest during cold and wet periods. These periods coincide with above-average frequencies of both floods and droughts in the lower Yangtze River, phenomena that are associated with locust outbreaks. Our results imply differential ecological responses to interdecadal and interannual climatic variability. Such frequency-dependent effects deserve increased attention in global warming studies. © 2007 by The National Academy of Sciences of the USA.","Agricultural pest; Ecological response; Frequency dependence; Global warming; Locusta migratoria manilensis","article; China; climate; drought; ecology; environmental temperature; flooding; greenhouse effect; locust; nonhuman; population dynamics; precipitation; priority journal; Animals; China; Chronobiology; Climate; Ecosystem; Grasshoppers; Greenhouse Effect; Natural Disasters; Population Dynamics; Time Factors; Locusta migratoria manilensis",,,,,,"Chen, Y.-L., (1999) The Locust and Grasshopper Pests of China, , China Forestry Publishing House, Beijing; (1982) The Locust and Grasshopper Agricultural Manual, , Centre for Overseas Pest Research , Centre Overseas Pest Res, London; Tanaka, S., Zhu, D.-H., (2005) Appl Entomol Zool, 40, pp. 257-263; Uvarov, B., (1977) Grasshoppers and Locusts: A Handbook of General Acridology, 2. , Cambridge Univ Press, Cambridge, UK; Farrow, R., (1984) J Aust Inst Agric Sci, 50, pp. 161-166; Zhang, Z., Li, D., (1999) Ecol Res, 14, pp. 267-270; Ma, S.-C., Ting, Y.-C., Li, D.-M., (1965) Acta Entomol Sin, 14, pp. 319-338; Tsao, C., (1950) Chin J Agric Res, 1, pp. 57-66; Ma, S.-C., (1958) Acta Entomol Sin, 8, pp. 1-40; Christensen, J.H., Hewitson, B., Busuioc, A., Chen, A., Gao, X., Held, I., Jones, R., Laprise, R., (2007) Climate Change 2007: The Physical Science Basis, Summary for Policy Makers, Contribution of Working Group I to the Fourth Assessment Report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change